  "summary": "## Summary: Combined Inbox Tabs with Pinning\n\n### Changes Implemented\n- **Combined tab bar**: Merged the folder tabs (Inbox, VIP, Newsletters, Spam, All), account filter chips, and label filter chips into a single unified tab bar\n- **Pinnable accounts**: Users can pin email accounts from the Account dropdown; pinned accounts appear as tabs in the bar with provider icon and truncated email name\n- **Pinnable labels**: Users can pin labels and smart labels from the Label dropdown; pinned labels appear as colored tabs in the bar with a color dot\n- **Account dropdown**: Added an \"Account\" dropdown button at the end of the tab bar that lists all accounts with pin/unpin toggle icons (pin icon fills when pinned, appears on hover when unpinned)\n- **Label dropdown**: Added a \"Labels\" dropdown button at the end of the tab bar that lists all labels and smart labels grouped by type, each with pin/unpin toggle icons\n- **Unpin from tabs**: Pinned tab items show an X icon on hover to unpin directly from the tab bar\n- **localStorage persistence**: Pinned accounts and labels are persisted in `localStorage` keys `inbox-pinned-accounts` and `inbox-pinned-labels`\n- **Visual separator**: A thin vertical line separates folder tabs from pinned items when any are pinned\n- **Click-outside-to-close**: Both dropdowns close when clicking outside them\n- **Mutual exclusivity**: Selecting a pinned account/label clears other filter types to prevent conflicting filters\n- **Active state highlighting**: The correct tab is highlighted based on which filter is active (folder tab only highlights when no account/label filter is active)\n- **Simplified filter panel**: Removed the account selector from the expanded filter panel (now handled by dropdown); kept date range filters\n\n### Files Modified\n- `app/(app)/inbox/page.tsx` — Added pinned tabs state management, combined tab bar UI with dropdowns, removed separate account/label filter chip rows\n\n### Notes for Developer\n- The mobile filter drawer (`InboxFilterDrawer`) is unchanged and still works for mobile users\n- Pinned state is per-browser (localStorage) — not synced across devices\n- The dropdowns are desktop-only (`hidden md:block`) since mobile uses the filter drawer\n- All existing folder functionality (VIP manage, Whitelist manage buttons) is preserved"
}